reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great fans, Needs a way to connect fans singly
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. EDIT: I changed my original rating from a 3 to a 5. I wrote to Asiahorse and Asiahorse’s customer service was super fast to explain about this being a new product release and that they are addressing this problem. They also are sending me the cables I need free of charge. I must say I was very impressed with how quickly this was resolved.EDIT2: I’ve included a video of my final build. Also pic showing the fan speeds and CPU temp at 1000rpm they are keeping my 5800X3D nice and cool. The fans are much quieter than my original ones and provide ample cooling as needed I haven’t seen my the notoriously hot CPU go over 75C since the update even with the big Aorus RTX4080 Master running cyberpunk2077 on ultra setting. I definitely recommend these fans and this company.Pros: The fans are great and the ARGB infinity lighting goes perfectly with my AIO cpu cooler. With the ability to use both the PWM and ARGB functions of your motherboard they really are nice. They also are quiet with good lighting effects. The airflow is pretty decent keeping my 5800X3D well within limits even while running a good workload.Cons: they are individual fans that are implied to be used as single or as a daisy chained set but in fact they can only be used as a set. They only supply 1 special proprietary fan/ARGB cable. So you can only connect 1 fan as a single, the other 2 are useless without a way to power them. I’ve spent an hour searching online and I haven’t found anything close to the cable input they use.I hated to do it but I gave them 3 stars because they are nice, but they don’t deserve a 4th or 5th with such a big problem that almost seems to be done intentionally forcing you to buy sets of 3 even if you only need 1 or 2 fans.Bottom line is if you’re looking for a 360 fan setup this is a nice option but if you want to split them up there are far better options available for much less money.EDIT: I just noticed all of the 5 star reviews on this are from compensated reviewers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Why no 140mm version?
reviews.reviewText: I love these fans and the aesthetic is exactly as advertised. I only wish they came in 140mm as I have multiple cases I’d like to buy white versions for but they don’t have holes for 120mm fans. Either way my personal system looks much better now. Very happy with them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great value for price
reviews.reviewText: Best bang for your buck rgb infinity style fans. However, already have an issue with a fan making a screeching noise when at high rpms. With it being a 3 pack, you have to buy 3 more to replace one faulty one or return all 3 and leave your pc without proper fan intake.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are legit
reviews.reviewText: I bought two packs of these babies and they are lovely! they do the job on my radiator and they work like a charm and also they look amazing, literally like the Lian Li one and even better to be honest on some colors. also they are very quiet and if you need to use only one fan just contact support and they will ship you an adapter. very cool will buy again!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Good fans but..
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. They push a lot of air and are pretty good fans but... the RGB didn't last long on them. I have one fan that has a mind of it's own and won't do a single solid color. I wish I could just message the seller directly and don't have to deal with Amazons automated return crap because these fans only come in 3s I just need to replace one fan. These have only been in use for maybe 3 weeks since I've finished my build.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great fans, missing one key component
reviews.reviewText: To start out, these fans will rival Uni Fans all day long. Easy to install and the simple power adapter allows all your fans to plug into one PWM and ARGB spot on your motherboard.Where this product falls short is if you want to use a single fan for rear exhaust or have a need for less than three fans, there are no extra power connectors to work with. It would be a shame to buy another 3 pack for just one fan and connector.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful, but as a 3-pack
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Absolutely love these fans - they look fantastic and are definitely quieter than others. I have a 3-pack of them as case fans, and barely hear them. By comparison, when the AIO cooler kicks in (different brand), it's 3 times louder. I'm going to buy another set of these and replace the AIO fans with them.They're well-made, solid white plastic, not flimsy at all. The infinity mirror effect adds a classy dimension to the whole thing.Only 1 cable to route, the other 2 fans daisy chain into the 1st one. HOWEVER, this is a problem if you want to split the set - you can only use 1 fan, the other 2 can't be connected.It's not a design flaw, it's something I should have considered before buying, but I want to point it out. If the manufacturer wants to make adapter cables to convert the proprietary daisy-chain plug to regular PWM + ARGB, that would be amazing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars 5 stars if your only going to use 3 fan together
reviews.reviewText: Look and perform great but must hook up all three no power cables for spitting up set, would be forced to buy another set in order to slip, searched for power cables and came up with nothing this would get 5 stars from me if I had gotten 3 power cables with the three fans, now missing one fan from case that I can not use because of missing power cable

These fans look amazing and perform well. My temps went down 8 Celsius overall after replacing my other case fans. The seller also responded pretty well to questions and concerns that I have. Overall, this case is recommended for people looking for affordable, great quality and awesome looking fans.
I bought 2 sets of 3 fans, only 2 of them were working. what a scam.
